&lt;p&gt;Description :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Archivo Black is a grotesque font from Omnibus-Type. It was originally designed for highlights and headlines. This family is reminiscent of late nineteenth century American typefaces. Archivo Narrow was designed to be used simultaneously in print and digital platforms. The technical and aesthetic characteristics of this typeface are both crafted for high performance typography.&lt;/p&gt;

